result.execSummary:
Isaac Terwey Pederson was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Isaac Terwey Pederson was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Bail/bond hearing on February 7, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

01:33 PM  Apprs: CO: S. Needham, Rpr: Kasten, Clerk: Lindabaur. ADA:  Michelle P Brekken   DF ATTY: Abrianna Dolfi and Kailtin Dippolito for today  DF:  Isaac Terwey Pederson appeared from jail.  Defendant qualifies for PD.  DE confirms address and DOB. Court informs Defendant of rights. Off record discussion between Atty Dippolito and Defendant. Defendant would like to waive right to extradition. S/T Defendant. Court questions Defendant. Court finds Defendant freely and voluntarily waives right to return to Anoka County, MN. Defendant and Court execute Waiver of Extradition. Court sets BBH in the event that Defendant is not picked up by Anoka County, MN. Adjourned at 1:38 PM.  gll  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for February 7, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
